						<summary>

						<p>On another hero-stone set up in the same place.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Parakēsarivarman, who took the head of Vīrapāṇḍya (Āditya II) Year 3: 963 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Records that when the village Tiruvūṟal Chōḷaṉūr was destroyed and its cattle were lifted Śāttayaṉ, the sluice-operator at Cheṅguṉṟam fought with that cattle lifter and died while rescuing the cattle. </p>						

						</summary>
